<paragraph blockId="47.[189,310,1390,1416]" box="[189,310,1390,1416]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1390,1416]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1390,1416]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,1398,1439,1654]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Clypeal posterior angle partially covering the canthus (
<figureCitation box="[863,977,1439,1465]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="36.[189,232,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,477,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[189,1398,452,1714]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Fig. 13. ♂♂. A. Head–prothorax dorsal, tarsus rotated laterally to apex. B–C. Mesotibia−tarsus (C, with details of tarsomere I and IV). D−G. Aedeagus (lateral, parameres apex). H. Metafemur. A–B, D–E. Pseudoserica marmorea Guérin-Méneville, 1831. C, F−H. Mallotarsus spadiceus Blanchard, 1850. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3832708/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
); pronotal anterior margin beaded, posterior margin not beaded and with two acute projections over the anterior elytron–scutellum contact, posterior angle acute (
<figureCitation box="[459,571,1514,1541]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="36.[189,232,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,477,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[189,1398,452,1714]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Fig. 13. ♂♂. A. Head–prothorax dorsal, tarsus rotated laterally to apex. B–C. Mesotibia−tarsus (C, with details of tarsomere I and IV). D−G. Aedeagus (lateral, parameres apex). H. Metafemur. A–B, D–E. Pseudoserica marmorea Guérin-Méneville, 1831. C, F−H. Mallotarsus spadiceus Blanchard, 1850. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3832708/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
); prosternum anteriorly concave (similar to 
<figureCitation box="[1106,1215,1514,1541]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1719,1745]" captionTargetBox="[195,1390,272,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[189,1398,265,1672]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 12. ♂♂. A. Head–prothorax dorsal, tarsus rotated laterally to apex. B. Antenna. C. Protibia−tarsus. D−I. Aedeagus (lateral, parameres apex). J. Metatibia. K. Head−prothorax, ventral. A, F−G. Euryaspis obesa (Burmeister, 1855) comb. nov. B−E. Euryapsis gaudichaudi Blanchard, 1850. H−J. Philochloenia amata nom. nov. K. Philochloenia castaneipennis (Guérin-Méneville, 1831) comb. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832706" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3832706/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 12K</figureCitation>
) or an anterior longitudinal carina; protibia with 1–3 external teeth and with or without spur; elytron with posterior margin not beaded; male mesotarsomere I with an internal hook-like spine (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1205,1590,1616]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="36.[189,232,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,477,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[189,1398,452,1714]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Fig. 13. ♂♂. A. Head–prothorax dorsal, tarsus rotated laterally to apex. B–C. Mesotibia−tarsus (C, with details of tarsomere I and IV). D−G. Aedeagus (lateral, parameres apex). H. Metafemur. A–B, D–E. Pseudoserica marmorea Guérin-Méneville, 1831. C, F−H. Mallotarsus spadiceus Blanchard, 1850. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3832708/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
); abdomen with intersegmental membrane VII–VIII concealed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,303,1696,1722]" box="[189,303,1696,1722]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1696,1722]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1696,1722]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,1399,1744,1846]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
The genus is recognized by having the posterior pronotal margin with two lateromedial teeth which project over the anterior elytron–scutellum contact. In addition, the male mesotarsomere I has a hooklike spine (
<figureCitation box="[317,423,1820,1846]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="36.[189,232,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,477,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[189,1398,452,1714]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Fig. 13. ♂♂. A. Head–prothorax dorsal, tarsus rotated laterally to apex. B–C. Mesotibia−tarsus (C, with details of tarsomere I and IV). D−G. Aedeagus (lateral, parameres apex). H. Metafemur. A–B, D–E. Pseudoserica marmorea Guérin-Méneville, 1831. C, F−H. Mallotarsus spadiceus Blanchard, 1850. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3832708/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
), that also occurs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1850" box="[663,805,1820,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Mallotarsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[663,805,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Mallotarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[821,925,1820,1846]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="36.[189,232,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[195,1395,477,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[189,1398,452,1714]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Fig. 13. ♂♂. A. Head–prothorax dorsal, tarsus rotated laterally to apex. B–C. Mesotibia−tarsus (C, with details of tarsomere I and IV). D−G. Aedeagus (lateral, parameres apex). H. Metafemur. A–B, D–E. Pseudoserica marmorea Guérin-Méneville, 1831. C, F−H. Mallotarsus spadiceus Blanchard, 1850. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3832708" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3832708/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
) and part of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LePeletier de Saint-Fargeau &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1828" box="[1074,1180,1821,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dicrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1074,1180,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Dicrania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1850" box="[1253,1381,1820,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dicrania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ebenina">
<emphasis box="[1253,1274,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1288,1381,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">ebenina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,1399,1888,2028]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
The present study revalidates 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1838" box="[550,708,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudoserica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[550,708,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Pseudoserica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, formerly a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LePeletier de Saint-Fargeau &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1828" box="[1014,1105,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Plectris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1014,1105,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Plectris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the following characters (opposition to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LePeletier de Saint-Fargeau &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1828" box="[502,593,1925,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Plectris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[502,593,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Plectris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): posterior pronotal margin with two lateromedial teeth over the anterior elytron–scutellum contact (margin straight); male mesotarsomere I with a hook-like spine (without spines); internal area of metatarsomere V without spine-like setae (with spine-like setae).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
